What do you say on a forum as impersonal as the internet esp. when you are seeking a soul mate ??... Well you put in what you think is your honest picture of yourself and hope (REALLY HARD) that there is someone out there who is looking for someone like you !!!

Anyway, I am a postgraduate who currently works in the FMCG sector and makes enough to ensure that he doesnt have to go hungry and undertake his other passions - Music and Traveling without having to think about what next? I love traveling, food, reading and music, not necessarily in the same order. I have few but very supportive friends who I know I can wake up in the middle of the night without hesitation and a fantastically awesome family that comprises my two younger brothers and my parents. These are people I can kill for and I know they would do the same for me. As for the rest, I have a lot of acquaintances as part of my job, but then who doesnt in today's world !!!

I am looking for a companion, someone who I can hold a conversation with and not someone who necessarily matches with me on a "list of criteria met", cause I honestly dont know who that person and what she would be doing? I am looking for someone who likes whats closest to my heart - Music & traveling coz I would like to share these moments with that special someone (else either the girl would get mad at the constant music playing around in the house or will run away with a more stable stay at home typa guy as I am constantly "planning", if not actually on a holiday somewhere). All the rest of it would probably be incidental if we can cross these fundamental but monumental hurdles;-)

Anyway wont make this into an autobiography so will let a few things be unsaid so that we have something to talk about incase someone does decide to get in touch !!! So here is hoping and crossing fingers :)
